        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 12 at 5:47PM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 547 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Grubbs, or 7 miles northeast of Newport, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Newport...                        Tuckerman...
Swifton...                        Grubbs...
Sedgwick...                       Stegall...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
